    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>A/B/C/D Check Requirements</title>
        <para>This Data Module defines the requirements and scope for major periodic maintenance checks under ATA Chapter 05.</para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Check Type Overview</title>
        <para>Periodic maintenance checks are classified into four major categories:</para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>A Check</title>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Frequency:</emphasis> Every 400-600 flight hours or 200-300 flight cycles</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Duration:</emphasis> 10-20 hours, typically performed overnight</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Visual inspections of aircraft systems</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Operational checks and lubrication</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Minor repairs and adjustments</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Fluid level checks and replenishment</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>B Check</title>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Frequency:</emphasis> Every 4-6 months or 1,000-1,500 flight hours</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Duration:</emphasis> 1-3 days in hangar</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>More detailed inspections than A Check</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Systems testing and functional checks</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Component replacements at life limits</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Landing gear and brake inspections</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>C Check</title>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Frequency:</emphasis> Every 18-24 months or 3,000-4,500 flight hours</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Duration:</emphasis> 1-2 weeks in hangar</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Comprehensive structural inspections</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Major component overhauls</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Access panel removal for internal inspections</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Corrosion prevention and treatment</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Flight control rigging and calibration</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>D Check</title>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Frequency:</emphasis> Every 6-10 years or 20,000-30,000 flight hours</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Duration:</emphasis> 1-2 months, complete aircraft teardown</para>
        <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Complete structural inspection and NDT</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Major systems overhaul and upgrade</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Interior refurbishment and modernization</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Avionics upgrade and recertification</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Paint stripping and repainting</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Integration with AAMMPP</title>
        <para>All check requirements are integrated with the Aerospace Assets Management, Maintenance and Procurement Platform (AAMMPP):</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Automated scheduling based on aircraft utilization</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Work package generation and resource planning</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Digital passport updates upon completion</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ESG impact tracking and reporting</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>ESG Considerations</title>
        <para>Each check type includes ESG metrics tracking:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Material waste and recycling rates</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Energy consumption during maintenance</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Chemical usage and environmental impact</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Worker safety and health monitoring</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Carbon footprint per maintenance event</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Compliance References</title>
        <para>
